A R E S O L U T I O N
Honoring Sidney First Presbyterian Church on its
Bicentennial.
WHEREAS, The members of the Senate of the 136th General Assembly 1
of Ohio are pleased to extend special recognition to Sidney First 2
Presbyterian Church on the memorable occasion of its Two Hundredth 3
Anniversary; and 4
WHEREAS, Sidney First Presbyterian Church has been an important 5
place of worship in the community since 1825, first serving area 6
residents in a log building that held the Shelby County seat, 7
courthouse, jail, and church before Sidney was an organized village 8
and eventually growing to the institution it is today. For the past 9
two centuries, this House of God has served as a tremendous source of 10
spiritual inspiration for its congregation, and it has encouraged 11
countless people to pursue lives of service, learning, and fellowship; 12
and 13
WHEREAS, This auspicious celebration offers the members of Sidney 14
First Presbyterian Church the opportunity to share their memories and 15
to reflect on the benefits of life in their close-knit community. 16
Under the guidance of many fine religious leaders, both past and 17
present, the parishioners have expanded on the best traditions of the 18
past to ensure a benevolent and prosperous future, and they can be 19
proud of the remarkable examples they have set through their values 20
and principles; and 21
WHEREAS, The members of Sidney First Presbyterian Church have 22
stood strong in the face of numerous challenges, and they have had a 23
positive impact on the lives of many local residents. Indeed, this 24
milestone represents their dedication and commitment to keep their 25
faith alive in the surrounding community, and all those associated 26

